com.inqwell.any

Class AnyByteArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.inqwell.any.AbstractAny
      • com.inqwell.any.AnyByteArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Any, Array, Composite, Vectored, Serializable, Cloneable

    public class AnyByteArray
extends AbstractAny
implements Array, Vectored, Cloneable
    Provides an Any abstraction for the JDK byte array. Seen as an Array by Inq.

        public boolean hasIdentity()
        Description copied from interface: Composite
        Determine whether a Composite instance is a managed object. Being managed means that hashCode() and equals() operate on the object instance itself rather than the instance's members. This means that the instance can be tracked where it is important to ensure that multiple threads are dealing with physically the same object.

        Most Composite implementations will return false with identity semantics being bestowed by suitable decorator. Note that

      • addByVector

        public void addByVector(int at,
                        Any value)
        Description copied from interface: Vectored
        Places the given value at the specified location in the collection. If the location is not in the range 0 to entries() then an exception is generated unless the collection can be sparse. If setSparse(true) has previously been called then place-holders are inserted as required.

        If the implementation is a map then a suitable key will be invented for the value, for example its identity.
